Note:
compiler/frontend/lexical/math_symbols.runa
Advanced Mathematical Symbol Support and Processing

This module provides comprehensive mathematical symbol functionality including:
- Greek letters (α, β, γ, δ, θ, λ, π, σ, φ, ψ, ω, etc.)
- Mathematical operators (∑, ∏, ∫, ∂, ∇, ∞)
- Set theory symbols (∈, ∉, ⊂, ⊆, ∪, ∩, ∅)
- Logic symbols (∀, ∃, ¬, ∧, ∨, ⊕)
- Comparison symbols (≤, ≥, ≠, ≈, ≡)
- Special functions (√, ∛, ⌊, ⌈, |)
- LaTeX-style escape sequence replacement (\alpha → α, \sum → ∑, etc.)
- Symbol validation and typo correction
- Context-aware symbol placement validation
- Performance optimized symbol processing
- Integration with lexer for seamless tokenization
- Symbol usage statistics and analysis
:End Note

Import "dev/debug/errors/core" as Errors

Note: =====================================================================
Note: MATHEMATICAL SYMBOL DATA STRUCTURES
Note: =====================================================================

Type called "MathSymbolMap":
    symbol_mappings as Dictionary[String, String]
    operator_mappings as Dictionary[String, String]
    function_mappings as Dictionary[String, String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, String]
    reverse_mappings as Dictionary[String, String]

Type called "SymbolReplacement":
    original_sequence as String
    unicode_symbol as String
    category as String
    description as String
    precedence as Integer
    usage_context as List[String]

Type called "SymbolValidation":
    position as Integer
    sequence as String
    is_valid as Boolean
    message as String
    suggestion as String
    severity as String

Type called "SymbolInfo":
    unicode_symbol as String
    escape_sequence as String
    category as String
    description as String
    usage_example as String
    mathematical_context as List[String]

Type called "MathSymbolProcessor":
    processor_id as String
    symbol_map as MathSymbolMap
    replacement_cache as Dictionary[String, String]
    validation_rules as List[String]
    statistics as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]

